Section 1:
1 L.D. 8
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 20, L.D. 8, “An Act Regarding the Term
10 of Appointment of Judicial Officers”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
12 'Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §6, as amended by PL 1991, c. 837, Pt. A, §7, is further amended
13 to read:
14 §6. Officials have 30 days to qualify
15 All public officers, other than judicial officers, appointed or renewed in accordance
16 with law shall, within 30 days after being commissioned, qualify to perform the duties of
17 their office and the certificate of qualification must be filed in the office of the Secretary of
18 State. Any officer who fails to qualify within 30 days and file a certificate of qualification
19 in the office of the Secretary of State within 45 days must be suspended by the Secretary
20 of State until the defect is corrected. During this suspension, the officer may be deemed to
21 have forfeited the appointment and the office may be declared vacant by the appointing
22 authority and a new appointment made.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment makes a conforming amendment to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title
2277 5, section 6 to clarify that it does not apply to judicial officers.
Page 1 - 132LR0280(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
